{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:58:04.741577+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:bJidiw | successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 503da61487c44c4a9f754b83f8dbf5ee1efdfb61)", "id": "lc_9fbfc09e-9e1d-40e8-a127-811b63d3e616"}, {"type": "text", "text": "| MCP:bJidiw | # pgdev — local PostgreSQL dev scaffold\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | A minimal, opinionated PostgreSQL setup for local development. **Not** for\n| MCP:bJidiw | production. The goal is to give a fresh checkout a working database with\n| MCP:bJidiw | migrations + seed data in two commands.\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Requirements\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | - Docker + docker compose v2\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Quickstart\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ```\n| MCP:bJidiw | cp .env.example .env\n| MCP:bJidiw | docker compose up -d\n| MCP:bJidiw | ./scripts/apply_migrations.sh\n| MCP:bJidiw | ./scripts/seed.sh\n| MCP:bJidiw | ```\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | After that, the database is reachable on `localhost:5432` with the user\n| MCP:bJidiw | configured in `.env` (default `app` / `app`).\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Database\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | - Image: `postgres:16-alpine`\n| MCP:bJidiw | - Listening port: **5432** (exposed to host)\n| MCP:bJidiw | - Data volume: `./.pgdata` (gitignored)\n| MCP:bJidiw | - Logging: configured in `config/postgresql.conf` (default: `log_statement = 'ddl'`)\n| MCP:bJidiw | - Auth: configured in `config/pg_hba.conf` (default: `scram-sha-256` for\n| MCP:bJidiw |   `host`, `trust` for local `unix_socket`)\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Migrations\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | Plain SQL files under `migrations/`, applied in lexicographic order by\n| MCP:bJidiw | filename. Use the `NNN_description.sql` convention starting at `001`.\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | The current set:\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | | File                        | Purpose                                |\n| MCP:bJidiw | |-----------------------------|----------------------------------------|\n| MCP:bJidiw | | `001_create_users.sql`      | Create `users` table.                  |\n| MCP:bJidiw | | `002_create_sessions.sql`   | Create `sessions` table, FK to users.  |\n| MCP:bJidiw | | `003_add_session_index.sql` | Add `idx_sessions_user_id` on sessions.|\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Seeds\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | Plain SQL files under `seeds/`, applied after migrations. See `seeds/README.md`.\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## Operations\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | See [`docs/operations.md`](docs/operations.md) for resetting, backups, and\n| MCP:bJidiw | common troubleshooting.\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | ## License\n| MCP:bJidiw | \n| MCP:bJidiw | MIT", "id": "lc_27b385f9-5d2e-4267-bcda-28a35a181890"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "07de22fd-0852-4506-95a0-544478e858da", "tool_call_id": "call_c8c976ee3e5f42be9f0250aa", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:58:18.258184+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here are the database migrations in the **rpnr-bench/T11_R01** repository, listed in the order they would be applied (lexicographic filename order):\n\n---\n\n### **Migration Order & Purpose**\n\n| # | File | Purpose | SQL Statement |\n|---|------|---------|---------------|\n| 1 | `migrations/001_create_users.sql` | Create the `users` table | `CREATE TABLE users (id BIGSERIAL PRIMARY KEY, email TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL, display_name TEXT, created_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now());` |\n| 2 | `migrations/002_create_sessions.sql` | Create the `sessions` table with a foreign key to `users` | `CREATE TABLE sessions (id UUID PRIMARY KEY, user_id BIGINT NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE, issued_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now(), expires_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL);` |\n| 3 | `migrations/003_add_session_index.sql` | Add an index on `sessions.user_id` for faster lookups | `CREATE INDEX idx_sessions_user_id ON sessions(user_id);` |\n\n---\n\n### **How They’re Applied**\n\nThe script `scripts/apply_migrations.sh` runs all `.sql` files in the `migrations/` directory in **lexicographic order** (by filename) against the PostgreSQL container (`pgdev_db`). The naming convention `NNN_description.sql` ensures the correct sequence.\n\n### **Key Observations**\n\n1. **Users first**: The `users` table is created before `sessions` because `sessions` references `users(id)`.\n2. **Index last**: The index on `sessions.user_id` is added after the table exists.\n3. **Foreign key cascade**: Deleting a user automatically deletes their sessions (`ON DELETE CASCADE`).\n4. **No down-migrations**: There are no rollback/down scripts; the setup is intended for local development only.\n\nThe README confirms this table and notes that seeds (initial test data) are applied separately via `scripts/seed.sh` after migrations.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 476, "prompt_tokens": 11042, "total_tokens": 11518, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 36, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10048}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "11f02860232a4b1da09a65c352e5da7f", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead88-cec7-71d3-92f9-69d8748d45dc-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11042, "output_tokens": 476, "total_tokens": 11518, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10048}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 36}}}}]}}}
